  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the tandoor to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a comal, cook the lamb shoulder over medium-high heat for 2 minutes per side, or until browned.",
    "Transfer the lamb to a plate and set aside.",
    "In the same comal, cook the onions and garlic over medium heat until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the coconut oil, massaman curry paste, cumin, coriander, salt, and black pepper to the comal, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the coconut milk to the comal, and bring to a simmer.",
    "Return the lamb shoulder to the comal, and cook for 10-12 minutes, or until the meat is tender and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Stir in the chopped cilantro, and serve the curry over rice."
